  "market_context": "Uptrend on USDEUR 4-hour chart with price near prior resistance at 0.9178–0.9182; analyst identifies a green candle as entry point for a hypothetical long trade.",
  "key_observation": "The ATR value on the entry candle was 0.0021, enabling objective risk management: stop-loss at 2×ATR (0.0042) and target at 2:1 R/R (0.0084).",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst opened the ATR indicator on the USDEUR 4H chart with default 14-period setting.",
    "Step 2: He identified the green candle as the intended long entry point and used a horizontal line to read the ATR value as 0.0021.",
    "Step 3: He calculated the stop-loss level as 2×ATR = 0.0042 below the entry price.",
    "Step 4: He set the take-profit target at 2:1 risk-to-reward, i.e., 2 × 0.0042 = 0.0084 above entry."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Using ATR provides objective, volatility-adjusted stop-loss and target levels, avoiding arbitrary placement and aligning risk with current market conditions.",
